        <content type="html" xml:base="https://Shanu-Kumawat.github.io/cc-website/blog/2025/graphql-vs-rest/">&lt;h2 id=&quot;the-api-debate&quot;&gt;The API Debate&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GraphQL has gained massive popularity, but is it always better than REST? Let&#x27;s compare objectively.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rest-api&quot;&gt;REST API&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple and well-understood&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great caching support&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with any HTTP client&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cons:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Over-fetching data&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple endpoints&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Versioning challenges&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;graphql&quot;&gt;GraphQL&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Request exactly what you need&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Single endpoint&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong typing&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-time with subscriptions&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cons:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Caching complexity&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning curve&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Query complexity limits&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;when-to-use-each&quot;&gt;When to Use Each&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Choose REST for simple CRUD apps. Choose GraphQL for complex data requirements with multiple clients.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
